1 2. “Charitable purpose” means religious, charitable,
2 scientific, literary, educational, artistic, cultural, economic
3 development, civic improvement, testing for public safety, research,
4 humanitarian, animal welfare, recreational, or environmental
5 protection purposes; to foster national or international amateur
6 sports competition, but only if no part of its activities involves
7 the provision of athletic facilities or equipment; to prevent
8 cruelty to children, the elderly, identified populations, or
