11 SECTION 8. AMENDATORY 18 O.S. 2021, Section 1029, is
12 amended to read as follows:
13 Section 1029.
14 LOANS TO EMPLOYEES AND OFFICERS; GUARANTY OF OBLIGATIONS
15 OF EMPLOYEES AND OFFICERS
16 Any A. Except as provided in subsection B of this section, any
17 corporation may lend money to, or guarantee any obligation of, or
18 otherwise assist any officer or other employee of the corporation or
19 of its subsidiary, including any officer or employee who is a
20 director of the corporation or its subsidiary whenever, in the
21 judgment of the directors, such loan, guaranty or assistance may
22 reasonably be expected to benefit the corporation. The loan,
23 guaranty or other assistance may be with or without interest, and
24 may be unsecured, or secured in such manner as the board of
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1534 Page 33

1 dire ctors shall approve, including, without limitation, a pledge of
2 shares of stock of the corporation. Nothing contained in this
3 section shall be construed to deny, limit or restrict the powers of
4 guaranty or warranty of any corporation at common law or under any
5 statute.
6 B. A charitable nonprofit corporation shall not lend money to
7 or guarantee the obligation of a director of the charitable
8 nonprofit corporation or of a related organization or of the spouse,
9 parents, children and spouses of children, brothers and sisters or
10 spouses of brothers and sisters of any director. If a loan is made
11 in violation of this section, the borrower’s liability remains. The
12 directors who approve a loan in violation of this section are
13 jointly and severally liable for its repayment.
14 SECTION 9. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
